A British soldier has been killed by an elephant during an anti-poaching operation in Malawi. Mathew Talbot, 22, of Coldstream Guards, was on patrol in Liwonde National Park on 5 May when he was charged by the animal. His commanding officer, Lt Col Ed Launders, described Guardsman Talbot as “determined and big-hearted”. Defence Secretary Penny Mordaunt said he served with “great courage and professionalism”. Gdsm Talbot was serving in his first operational deployment, the defence ministry said.  Military destroys 7 insurgents’ camps, rescues 25 more women, kids Soldiers kill 60 more B/Haram fighters, capture commander 7 terrorists’ camps destroyed, many rescued  –DHQ Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin